*fmod*

(PHP 4 >= 4.2.0, PHP 5, PHP 7, PHP 8)

fmod â€” Returns the floating point remainder (modulo) of the division of the
arguments

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  fmod(float $num1, float $num2): float~

Returns the floating point remainder of dividing the dividend ({num1}) by the
divisor ({num2}). The remainder (r) is defined as: num1 = i * num2 + r, for
some integer i. If {num2} is non-zero, r has the same sign as {num1} and a
magnitude less than the magnitude of {num2}.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{num1}

  The dividend

{num2}

  The divisor

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

The floating point remainder of {num1}/{num2}

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 Using fmod()

<?php >
  $x = 5.7;
  $y = 1.3;
  $r = fmod($x, $y);
  // $r equals 0.5, because 4 * 1.3 + 0.5 = 5.7
<?>

